article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Anthony Pritchard scored 22 points as Central Michigan beat South Florida 68-63 on Wednesday night. Pritchard also contributed six rebounds, five assists, and three steals for the Chippewas (1-3). Markus Harding scored 13 points while shooting 4 of 5 from the field and 4 for 6 from the line, and added five rebounds. Paul McMillan IV was 4 of 8 shooting (2 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 10 points. Chris Youngblood finished with 20 points for the Bulls (1-1). Selton Miguel added 16 points and three steals for South Florida. Corey Walker Jr. also had nine points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
